revisions.rev:
''Jih-chi chiu-chung'' ('''''Nine Diaries''''') was the most popular book published by [[China|Chinese]] writer [[Yu Dafu]]. Written in 1927, it detailed the events of his affair with the leftist writer Wang Ying-hsia and broke all previous Chinese sales records.

